<typeStatus id="54848873FFD7FFF5FB7C27DBFE93FB4D" box="[260,313,1232,1258]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5FBD227DBFC94FB4D" authority="Jullien, 1881" authorityName="Jullien" authorityYear="1881" box="[426,830,1232,1258]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Chaperiidae" genus="Chaperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5FBD227DBFD38FB4E" box="[426,658,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Chaperia australis</emphasis>
Jullien, 
<number id="3DF724F6FFD7FFF5F88627DBFC94FB4D" box="[766,830,1232,1258]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1881.0">1881</number>
</taxonomicName>
, is generally considered to be a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5FB5327FEFD71FAA8" authority="Lamouroux, 1824" authorityName="Lamouroux" authorityYear="1824" box="[299,731,1269,1295]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Flustridae" genus="Flustra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="acanthina">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5FB5327FEFE55FAA9" box="[299,511,1269,1294]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Flustra acanthina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B20FFD7FFF5F87F27FEFD71FAA8" author="Lamouroux" box="[519,731,1269,1295]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Lamouroux, J. V. F. (1824 - 26) Description des polypiers flexibles. In: Quoy, J. R. C. &amp; Gaimard, J. P. (Eds.), Voyage autour du Monde … execute sur l'Uranie et la Physicienne pendant les annees 1817 - 1820. Vol. 3, Zoologie IV. Pilet Aine, Paris, pp. 603 - 642." type="journal article" year="1824">
Lamouroux, 
<number id="3DF724F6FFD7FFF5F8D827FEFD71FAA8" box="[672,731,1269,1295]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1824.0">1824</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B20FFD7FFF5F96227FEFBFDFAA8" author="Hayward" box="[794,1111,1269,1295]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Hayward, P. J. &amp; Cook, P. L. (1983) The South African Museum's Meiring Naude Cruises. Part 13, Bryozoa II. Annals of the South African Museum, 91, 1 - 161." type="journal article" year="1983">
Hayward and Cook (
<number id="3DF724F6FFD7FFF5FE6927FEFBE4FAA8" box="[1041,1102,1269,1295]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1983.0">1983</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for nomenclatural history]. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B20FFD7FFF5FAEF2611FEFAFA93" author="Marcus" box="[151,336,1306,1332]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Marcus, E. (1955) Notas sobre briozoos marinhos Brasileiros. Arquivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro, 42 (1), 273 - 341." type="journal article" year="1955">
Marcus (
<number id="3DF724F6FFD7FFF5FB7E2611FEEDFA93" box="[262,327,1306,1332]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1955.0">1955</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported and illustrated a species from south of Vitória, Espírito Santo state, which he attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5FB55264BFE6FFAFE" box="[301,453,1344,1369]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Flustridae" genus="Flustra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="acanthina">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5FB55264BFE6FFAFE" box="[301,453,1344,1369]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">C. acanthina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but his material had four distal spines and a pair of proximolateral spines and thus cannot belong to this species; 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5FB81266EFD3BFAD9" box="[505,657,1381,1406]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Flustridae" genus="Flustra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="acanthina">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5FB81266EFD3BFAD9" box="[505,657,1381,1406]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">C. acanthina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<typeStatus id="54848873FFD7FFF5F97D266EFC9DFAD8" box="[773,823,1381,1407]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
locality [Falkland (
<collectingCountry id="F3287641FFD7FFF5FE67266EFB3AFAD8" box="[1055,1168,1381,1407]" name="Falkland Islands" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Malvinas</collectingCountry>
) Islands] has six distal spines and no proximal ones (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B20FFD7FFF5FB832681FD35FA03" author="Gordon" box="[507,671,1418,1444]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Gordon, D. P. (1986) The marine fauna of New Zealand: Bryozoa: Gymnolaemata (Ctenostomata and Cheilostomata Anasca) from the western south Island continental shelf and slope. New Zealand Oceanographic Institute Memoir, 95, 1 - 121." type="journal article" year="1986">
Gordon 
<number id="3DF724F6FFD7FFF5F8272681FD35FA03" box="[607,671,1418,1444]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, the material recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B20FFD7FFF5FE522681FB70FA03" author="Marcus" box="[1066,1242,1418,1444]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Marcus, E. (1955) Notas sobre briozoos marinhos Brasileiros. Arquivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro, 42 (1), 273 - 341." type="journal article" year="1955">
Marcus (
<number id="3DF724F6FFD7FFF5FEEB2681FB7BFA03" box="[1171,1233,1418,1444]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1955.0">1955</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5FF7A2680FA36FA03" box="[1282,1436,1419,1444]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Flustridae" genus="Flustra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="acanthina">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5FF7A2680FA36FA03" box="[1282,1436,1419,1444]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">C. acanthina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represents a new, undescribed species. The only other geographically close congeners are 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5FEB826BBFE93FA48" authority="Busk, 1884" authorityName="Busk" authorityYear="1884" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Chaperiidae" genus="Chaperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5FEB826BBFA31FA6E" box="[1216,1435,1456,1481]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Chaperia capensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B20FFD7FFF5FAE726DEFE9AFA48" author="Busk" box="[159,304,1493,1519]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Busk, G. (1884) Report on the Polyzoa collected by H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 76. Part I, The Cheilostomata. Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H. M. S. Challenger, Zoology, 10 (30), xxiv 1 - 216, 36 pls." type="journal article" year="1884">
Busk, 
<number id="3DF724F6FFD7FFF5FA9726DEFE9AFA48" box="[239,304,1493,1519]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1884.0">1884</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5FB3E26DEFD76FA48" authority="Kluge, 1914" authorityName="Kluge" authorityYear="1914" box="[326,732,1493,1519]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Chaperiidae" genus="Chaperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="polygonia">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5FB3E26DEFD90FA49" box="[326,570,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Chaperia polygonia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B20FFD7FFF5F83B26DEFD76FA48" author="Kluge" box="[579,732,1493,1519]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Kluge, G. A. (1914) Die Bryozoen der Deutschen Sudpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903. I. Die Familien Aeteidae, Cellularidae, Bicellaridae, Farciminaridae, Flustridae, Membraniporidae and Cribrilinidae. Deutsch Sudpolar- Expedition XV, Zoology, 7, 599 - 678, pls 27 - 34." type="journal article" year="1914">
Kluge, 
<number id="3DF724F6FFD7FFF5F8E526DEFD76FA48" box="[669,732,1493,1519]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1914.0">1914</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5F96626DEFF7FF9B3" authority="Florence, Hayward &amp; Gibbons, 2007" authorityName="Florence, Hayward &amp; Gibbons" authorityYear="2007" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Chaperiidae" genus="Chaperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="septispina">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5F96626DEFBBEFA49" box="[798,1044,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Chaperia septispina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE4B20FFD7FFF5FE6526DEFF7FF9B3" author="Florence" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Florence, W. K., Hayward, P. J. &amp; Gibbons, M. J. (2007). Taxonomy of shallow-water Bryozoa from the west coast of South Africa. African Natural History, 3, 1 - 58." type="journal article" year="2007">
Florence, Hayward &amp; Gibbons, 
<number id="3DF724F6FFD7FFF5FAEF26F1FF7FF9B3" box="[151,213,1530,1556]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, all from 
<collectingCountry id="F3287641FFD7FFF5FB3226F1FE42F9B3" box="[330,488,1530,1556]" name="South Africa" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5FB8C26F0FD79F9B3" box="[500,723,1531,1556]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Chaperiidae" genus="Chaperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5FB8C26F0FD79F9B3" box="[500,723,1531,1556]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Chaperia capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only two distal spines, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5FE5826F0FB11F9B3" box="[1056,1211,1531,1556]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Chaperiidae" genus="Chaperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="polygonia">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5FE5826F0FB11F9B3" box="[1056,1211,1531,1556]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">C. polygonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
five or six, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5FFF926F0FEA4F99E" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Chaperiidae" genus="Chaperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="septispina">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5FFF926F0FEA4F99E" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">C. septispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seven spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8036D1FFD7FFF5FABE254EFA20F968" blockId="5.[151,1437,1157,1780]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Our specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5FBDE254EFDF9F9F9" box="[422,595,1605,1630]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Chaperiidae" genus="Chaperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5FBDE254EFDF9F9F9" box="[422,595,1605,1630]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">C. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are of non-attached transported fragments and hence slightly eroded, which renders the precise number of spine bases uncertain. Judging from the convex shapes of the specimens, with down-curving edges, they appear to have been growing on a non-durable substratum ― perhaps a sponge or ascidian, which was partly overgrown by another bryozoan that was in turn overgrown by 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D52FFD7FFF5FEA225BEFA29F969" box="[1242,1411,1717,1742]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Chaperiidae" genus="Chaperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="B94BEAC3FFD7FFF5FEA225BEFA29F969" box="[1242,1411,1717,1742]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">C. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
